Reasoning: The paper discusses the synthesis of distributed systems using a formal proof development system, which suggests it may belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The use of event theory and the focus on distributed protocols suggests it may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of a high-level specification language, which could place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The focus on synthesis and the use of a proof development system suggests it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the conversion of knowledge-based protocols to ordinary protocols, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
